&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Details on Beastlord list #1 part A&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;All throughout beta there were three PH spells for Beastlords that at the end of beta simply poofed.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;There have been many suggestions made for what spells could be added...&lt;xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" &gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;A new slow spell at 70.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Keep the slow % the same as Shaman’s revenge, but add a negative resist mod to the spell.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Beastlords are having a hard time slowing in a growing number of places.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;One of the main things we bring to a group is the ability to slow, but we simply aren't performing it to a reasonable degree in certain spots.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;There are times where a beastlord can chain cast slow and never get it to stick before a mob dies.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;A self only buff.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The only self-only buff Beastlords get is "frenzy" a low level shaman spell that we got back at level 49.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Some of the main suggestions for this buff are: +double atk mod, +dmg mod, +avoidance mod, +mana regen.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;A new debuff&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Our last debuff was incapacitate at level 56.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Either upgrading the line or adding a new type of Beastlord debuff that stacked with other debuffs would be a nice addition to our current omens line up.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;A de-agro type of spell.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Beastlords simply generate too much agro for the damage they are doing.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;We are the only melee in the game outside of paladins and warriors that don't get some way (via AA or skill) to lower our agro.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;Group infusion of spirit.&amp;nbsp; This spell was highly requested by beastlords, but where it came from in GoD made it almost useless to those that could actually get it.&amp;nbsp; Now that omens is out and the stat caps are going up again a lot of beastlords could use the spell if it were put at level 66.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
